FBIS3-15401 "drsov044_h_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 Moldova Russian Gas Supplies To Continue Despite Nonpayments LD0403152294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1430 GMT 4 Mar 94 LD0403152294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Moldova has managed to persuade Russian gas suppliers not to resort to extreme measures, like cutting off gas supplies because of nonpayments, stated Boris Karandyuk, director general of Moldova's state department on gas supplies. Yesterday he held talks on settling Chisinau's gas debt to Russia with Gazprom managers. Chisinau will clear its debt by supplying goods, particularly agricultural goods.
